.box.text
  %h2
    About
  %p
    The goal of this project is to create a 
    %b lightweight, extensible, modular JavaScript UI framework / library
    , which uses the MooTools class architecture and has elements that are rearly seen in other libraries, but used in desktop applications or in mobile device UIs. 
  %hr
  %h2
    Compability
  %p
    This project currently doesn't support IE due to an IE specific issue. It will be resolved in the first release candidate.
  %p
    Targeted browsers:
  %ul
    %li
      Chrome 7+
    %li
      Firefox 3.1+
    %li
      Opera 9.6+
    %li
      IE6+
    %li
      Safari 3.1+
  %hr
  %h2
    Dependencies
  %p
    Mootools 1.3, some Canvas implementation for IE (ExplorerCanvas)
  %hr
  %h2
    Languages
  %p
    Lattice is built with CoffeeScript, packaged with Ruby. Themes are created with SASS.
  %hr
  %h2
    Side projects
  %p
    There are a few new projects that resulted of the development of this project which this site uses. (links will be available when they reach a more or less stable state)
  %ul
    %li
      Packager implementation for Ruby, that supports both JavaScript nad CoffeeScript.
    %li
      MooTools class documentation creator in Ruby that supports extends, implements, delegates, attributes, events, properties, using YAML.
    
